A company uses AWS Organizations with SCPs. The following SCP is attached to the Production OU:

{"Effect":"Deny","Action":"s3:DeleteBucket","Resource":"*"}

An IAM administrator in a member account has an IAM policy granting s3:* on all resources. They attempt to delete an S3 bucket and receive AccessDenied. A colleague in the management account with the same IAM policy successfully deletes a bucket. Why does the administrator fail while the colleague succeeds?

An application uses KMS to encrypt data. The CMK has the following key policy statement:

{"Effect":"Allow","Principal":{"AWS":"arn:aws:iam::123456789012:root"},"Action":"kms:*","Resource":"*"}

A developer's IAM policy denies kms:Decrypt. The developer attempts to call KMS Decrypt. What happens?
